The spin correlations in the pair of $	au$ leptons produced in high-energy proton-proton collisions are studied. The invariant mass of the $	au$-lepton pair is chosen close to the Z-boson mass; in these conditions, Z-bos on exchange gives the dominant contribution to the Drell-Yan mechanism. The interaction of Z bosons with $	au$ leptons, in addition to the Standard Model couplings, can include weak anomalous magnetic and electric dipole moments (or form factors) of the $	au$ lepton. The dependence of elements of the pp spin-correlation matrix on the weak anomalous moments is determined for various regions of the rapidity of the $	au$-lepton pair. Based on this calculation, we construct a semirealistic observable built on the momenta of pions in the $	au^{\mp} 	o \pi^{\mp} 
u_{	au}$ and $	au^{\pm} 	o ho^{\pm} 
u_{	au} 	o \pi^{\pm} \pi^{0} 
u_{	au}$ decay channels, and we show that this observable can be sensitive to the weak anomalous dipole moments.
